PCs fire around 70Hz, glutamatergic CNCs around
20Hz, some GABAergic CNCs around 5Hz, granule cell around 2Hz

PURKINJE CELLS
- MFR 60-100 Hz
- CCG : very regular (Gao, Lena et al., 2012)
CCG peak : 200-500Hz
- WVF : very deep

MOLECULAR LAYER INTERNEURONS
Jörntell et al., 2010
- MFR : 20 Hz (ISI histogram)
- CCG : quite regular
CCG peak : <100Hz

GRANULE CELLS
Jörntell et al., 2006
- MFR : 2Hz
- CCG : bursting, low baseline FR
CCG peak : >200Hz

DCN CELLS 
Canto et al., 2016 : whole cell properties of Cerebellar Nuclei Neurons in vivo
- MFR : 20 to 60 Hz, different cell types
- Regular, mirror to PKJ activity (time-locked spiking, Raman 2012)
<- differentiated from MLI/PKJ thanks to depth (phy)
dk50 : undr channel 80
dk68 : 

GOLGI CELLS
- MFR : 9 +/- 5 Hz (Kanichay et al., 2008)
- CCG : Gao, Lena et al., 2012
